description: Tropical Storm Rafael formed in the Caribbean on Monday and is forecast to become a hurricane on Tuesday. It could approach the U.S. by mid to late week.
title: Tropical Storm Rafael forms in the Caribbean and is expected to become a hurricane

description: Across the world, all eyes are on the election battle between former President Donald Trump and Vice President which will have implications for almost everyone.
title: All eyes are on America as an uncertain world awaits critical election result

description: The head of Myanmar’s military government will pay an official visit this week to China, the Southeast Asian nation’s most important international ally.
title: Head of Myanmar’s military government to visit close ally China

description: Iranian authorities have detained a young woman who was seen walking around the Islamic Azad University in Tehran in her underwear, in what activists say was a protest against enforcement of the country’s strict dress code.
title: Iran detains woman who stripped to her underwear in apparent protest at Tehran university

description: Storms in eastern Spain that led to massive flooding last week and killed more than 200 people, mostly near Valencia, have now dumped rain on Barcelona.
title: Heavy rains batter Barcelona as search for flood victims goes on in Valencia

description: An Israeli court on Sunday partially lifted a gag order on a case investigating leaks of classified Gaza documents suspected to involve one of Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu’s media advisers.
title: Netanyahu under fire after judge lifts gag order on leaks that may have harmed hostage talks

description: Unprecedented air pollution levels in Pakistan’s second-largest city of Lahore prompted authorities to take emergency measures, including closing schools.
title: Lahore air pollution hits historic high, forcing school closures

description: The size of China’s highly anticipated stimulus plans will likely depend on the outcome of the U.S. presidential election, analysts said.
title: China gears up for a big week as markets await U.S. elections and stimulus details

description: A young woman stripped to her underwear at an Iranian university in an apparent protest against the country's strict Islamic dress code, according to online videos and media reports. A video posted on social media showed the woman outside a department of the Islamic Azad University.
title: Woman strips to her underwear in an apparent protest at a Tehran university

description: A U.S. citizen who was spirited out of eastern Ukraine by Russian special forces after helping the Kremlin target Ukrainian troops said in Moscow on Saturday he had asked for Russian citizenship.
title: U.S. citizen who  helped Russia from Ukraine appears in Moscow

description: Details are emerging about suspected leaked intelligence documents after an Israeli court lifted a gag order and said the leak may have caused serious damage to the state’s security and could have hurt efforts to release the hostages held in Gaza. One of the suspects behind the leaks is a media advisor to the Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. NBC News' Claudio Lavanga has the latest details on Early Today.
title: Israeli army confirms classified and sensitive intelligence was leaked

description: Eight people are going on trial in Paris on terrorism charges Monday over the beheading of teacher Samuel Paty, who was killed by an Islamic extremist after showing caricatures of Islam’s prophet to his middle school students for a lesson on freedom of expression.
title: France holds trial over the beheading of a teacher who showed prophet cartoons to his class

description: Moldova’s pro-Western President Maia Sandu has won a second term in a pivotal presidential runoff against a Russia-friendly opponent, in a race that was overshadowed by claims of Russian interference, voter fraud, and intimidation in the European Union candidate country.
title: Moldova’s pro-Western president wins 2nd term in runoff overshadowed by Russian meddling claims

description: At least nine people died after Mount Lewotobi Laki-Laki in eastern Indonesia erupted on Sunday, spewing explosive plumes of lava officials said Monday.
title: Indonesia’s Laki-Laki volcano erupts, killing 9 people

description: A tropical disturbance in the Caribbean is likely to become a hurricane as it passes over Cuba and into the Gulf of Mexico by midweek, federal forecasters said Sunday.
title: Caribbean disturbance likely to become hurricane before it moves into Gulf
